==English==

===Noun===
'''facebook'''  (''plural:'' '''facebooks''')

# A [[book]] made up of individuals' [[photographs]] and names; often published at the start of the academic year by [[university]] [[administrations]] with the intention of helping [[students]] to get to know each other better.
#:''The shipment of facebooks be distributed to the freshman at orientation.''

===Derived terms===
* [[freshman]] facebook

===Related terms===
A facebook may be contrasted with a [[yearbook]], which is traditionally published at the end of the academic year and usually includes details about various aspects of the preceding year, along with the sort of content one would find in a facebook.

